This presidential memorandum, issued on March 20, 2017, delegates authority to the Secretary of State under the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2017. The memorandum states that the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 3132 of the Act are now delegated to the Secretary of State. The memorandum also mentions that any reference to the Act in this memorandum should be considered as a reference to any future Act that is the same or substantially the same as the provision mentioned. Lastly, it authorizes and directs the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Donald J. Trump.